             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am a widow; I lost a shirt on Friday the 20th of January; I hung out several shirts between eleven and twelve; I saw they were all there; I missed one shirt between three and four; I suspected 
               <persName id="t17920215-21-person321">
                  Peter
                   Millar
               <interp inst="t17920215-21-person321" type="surname" value="Millar"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17920215-21-person321" type="given" value="Peter"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17920215-21-person321" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            ; the constable found the shirt; he said he meant to bring it to me on the morrow morning; it was tucked in between the lath and plaster, in his bed-room; the constable took it out; I was present; I said, that is my shirt, it is marked with two F's; I am a washerwoman; the constable has had it from that time to this.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17920215-21-person322">
                  THOMAS
                   PERKINS
               <interp inst="t17920215-21-person322" type="surname" value="PERKINS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17920215-21-person322" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17920215-21-person322" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>(Produces the shirt.) I took it from the boy's room.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>Please you, my Lord, I met a man in Hampstead, and he asked me if there was a pawnbroker's in the town; I said, no; he said, I have got a shirt to sell for 2 s.; he asked me to buy it; I said, I would ask the coachman; I took it to the coachman, and he said he would lend me 2 s. to buy it for myself, as he did not want any thing of the kind.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17920215-21-verdict118" type="verdictDescription">
